Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning (RL) algorithms, specifically neural Monte-Carlo-Tree-Search (neural MCTS), to solve combinatorial optimization problems. This falls under the domain of AI research.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses RL algorithms, which are a subset of machine learning, to solve combinatorial optimization problems. 
3. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper proposes the Zermelo Gamification (ZG) to transform combinatorial optimization problems into Zermelo games, which is a concept from game theory. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper deals with combinatorial optimization problems, which are a class of problems that require efficient algorithms and data structures to solve. 
5. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper proposes a specially designed neural MCTS for solving Zermelo games, which involves programming and implementation of the algorithm.
